  "description": "800ms Gaussian grains at density=5 with maximum smear (smearAmount=0.95, smearMix=0.85). The smear effect stretches each grain's spectral content horizontally — 800ms grains blurred further by spectral smear produce a pressure sensation in the low-mids. Filter at 1200Hz. At 12 voices, 60 grains/minute total: each note triggers a slow geological event. The column of water above is palpable.",
  "tags": ["pressure", "smear", "submerged", "gaussian", "800ms", "low-frequency", "geological"],
